@page "/projects"

<PageTitle>Projects</PageTitle>

<section class="page-header">
    <span class="section-kicker">Projects</span>
    <h1>Student Builds And Practice Work</h1>
    <p>
        These are sample projects that reflect the kind of work I enjoy creating while building my skills in
        programming, UI design, and teamwork.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="feature-grid">
    <article class="tech-card project-card">
        <span class="project-tag">Web App</span>
        <h2>Campus Event Tracker</h2>
        <p>
            I designed this responsive web project to organize school events, view schedules, and track attendance
            updates for student activities.
        </p>
        <div class="project-meta">HTML, CSS, C#, Blazor basics</div>
    </article>

    <article class="tech-card project-card">
        <span class="project-tag">Database</span>
        <h2>Library Record System</h2>
        <p>
            I created this simple student system concept to manage book inventory, borrower records, and return dates
            using beginner-friendly database design principles.
        </p>
        <div class="project-meta">SQL, forms, CRUD workflow</div>
    </article>

    <article class="tech-card project-card">
        <span class="project-tag">UI Concept</span>
        <h2>Study Buddy Mobile Mockup</h2>
        <p>
            I created this prototype mobile interface to help students manage tasks, deadlines, and shared group
            study sessions in one place.
        </p>
        <div class="project-meta">Figma, user flow, wireframing</div>
    </article>

    <article class="tech-card project-card">
        <span class="project-tag">Team Project</span>
        <h2>Barangay Information Portal</h2>
        <p>
            I worked on this collaborative concept website focused on announcements, public service information, and
            digital access to local community updates.
        </p>
        <div class="project-meta">Collaboration, planning, frontend layout</div>
    </article>
</section>
